42
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:05,359
You'll be born exactly the same
as yourself in your next life.

43
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:08,930
And you'll live exactly
the same life as you're living.

44
00:02:13,069 --> 00:02:14,509
It'll be repeated infinitely.

45
00:02:18,979 --> 00:02:21,250
You know I don't bluff, right?

46
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:23,780
I'm off now.

47
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:28,389
Think wisely.

48
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,659
Gosh, why do they make me
live the same exact life?

49
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,340
I'd hate that.

50
00:02:47,439 --> 00:02:48,539
He must've made it up.

51
00:02:50,710 --> 00:02:52,939
There's no such harsh hell!

52
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,719
It can't be true.

53
00:03:08,530 --> 00:03:10,229
Your nose is really swollen.

54
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:12,860
Go away.

55
00:03:13,669 --> 00:03:14,729
Okay.

56
00:03:16,129 --> 00:03:18,270
- Hey, part-timer.
- Yes, Detective?

57
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:19,639
You go to
the Catholic church, right?

58
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:22,240
Yes, both my baptismal
and actual name is Yo Han.

59
00:03:22,509 --> 00:03:24,240
I didn't ask you that.

60
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,650
Do you know what kind of place
hell is?

61
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:33,750
Hell isn't where you are
burned or your limbs...

62
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:34,949
